episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: When an elite assassin carries out a kill, it catches the attention of an intelligence officer, who starts to hunt him down.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: With his client backing out of payment, the Jackal's reputation is on the line, and he starts to plot his revenge.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Armed with the knowledge of his wayward client's identity, the Jackal tracks him down in Munich, determined to settle the score.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: His vengeance fulfilled, the Jackal flees Munich and tries to quell Nuria's suspicions. Bianca follows a new lead in her hunt.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: The Jackal visits Norman with a special commission... but with Bianca also tracking Norman down, she is starting to close in on him.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Following his shootout with Bianca, the Jackal must escape his captors and regroup ahead of his next hit, as Bianca follows his trail.

episodes.name: Episode 7

episodes.name: Split in Two
episodes.overview: 2030: in a gray and hyper-controlled Milan, Diana and Luca are sent on a mission to Lugano to spy on the exchange of a powerful weapon. Not far away, Edo Zani, Manticore Italy's heir, has to respond to an unexpected proposal from the head of Manticore France, Cecile. In the flashbacks, Diana investigates her parents' suspicious deaths when she meets Gabriele, a mysterious Citadel agent.

episodes.name: War
episodes.overview: Diana and Edo form a secret agreement and make their first move, but they underestimate Cecile's fierce reaction. While Manticore Italy is under attack, Ettore Zani has to step in to stop a war from breaking out. In the flashbacks, Diana completes her training with Gabriele and becomes a Citadel agent.

episodes.name: Together
episodes.overview: Ettore sends Edo and Diana to Sicily on a sensitive mission that threatens their alliance. However, under the Mediterranean sun, the two discover they are connected by much more than their objectives. Eight years earlier, Diana infiltrates Manticore and carries out her first mission.

episodes.name: The Zanis
episodes.overview: Diana is captured and struggles desperately to survive while Ettore has to make a hard decision in order to restore Manticore Italy's power, as memories resurface of the day when his relationship with Edo was shattered forever.

episodes.name: Attack
episodes.overview: Edo leads a group of agents in an attack on the Manticore France's headquarters in Paris. Just as Diana is about to get her hands on the weapon, she is forced to decide which side she is on, as she had to do eight years earlier, the night Citadel was destroyed.

episodes.name: Jupiter
episodes.overview: As Diana ponders her choice, Edo works on a powerful new weapon. Ettore tries to get closer to his son, playing one last, surprise card. In a flashback, the Zanis mourn Enrico while Diana realizes she's the last living Citadel agent.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: When a terrorist group led by the villainous Jacob Pearce attacks a high-profile event, with the French Minister of Defence as their target, protection officer Vincent Taleb finds himself working with street-smart MI6 operative Zara Taylor to save the day. But when events take a dark turn, Vincent and Zara soon realize that the plan extends beyond just one politician. When they suspect that one of their colleagues in the security services is feeding information to Jacob, Vincent and Zara find themselves needing to rely only on each other. Increasingly isolated and with Jacob always one step ahead, can this unlikely pair stop Paris from falling to a man hell-bent on vengeance?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Vincent Taleb, close protection officer of Defense Minister Philippe Bardin, is deployed after an attack on the British embassy in Paris.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Vincent and Zara join an anti-terrorist task force set up to dismantle Pearce's group.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Jacob Pearce's mission for vengeance leads him to the people behind the attack that changed his life forever.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Vincent is still rocked by the revelation of the connection between Juliette and Pearce – will he be able focus on what really matters?

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Pearce gives Juliette a terrifying deadline, but an investigative breakthrough puts Zara and Vincent back on top.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Jacob Pearce is at last in custody, but he still has one last card to play and he unleashes the full scale of his operation to escape.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Following Pearce's ultimatum, Zara and Vincent attempt a last-ditch effort to convert one of Jacob's allies.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: With Jacob Pearce's plan in motion, and the bomb's detonation imminent, Zara, Vincent and Juliette fear they must surrender.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The infamous Agatha Harkness finds herself down and out of power after a suspicious goth Teen helps break her free from a distorted spell. Her interest is piqued when he begs her to take him on the legendary Witches' Road, a magical gauntlet of trials that, if survived, rewards a witch with what they're missing. Together, Agatha and this mysterious Teen pull together a desperate coven, and set off down, down, down the Road...

episodes.name: Seekest Thou the Road
episodes.overview: In small town Westview, Detective Agnes' murder case sends her down a road that changes everything.

episodes.name: Circle Sewn with Fate / Unlock Thy Hidden Gate
episodes.overview: With old foes in hot pursuit, Agatha and Teen gather a desperate coven to walk The Witches' Road.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Ha Yoon-seo has worked hard her whole life: after raising her younger brother alone, she is now a marketing manager at a credit card company. Her life takes a dramatic turn when she discovers that her boyfriend, Seo Ju-won, is the heir to the family that owns the company! Upon learning of their relationship, Ju-won's mother offers Yoon-seo money to break up with him, and Yoon-seo accepts. However, Ju-won is determined to win her back and will stop at nothing to reclaim her heart. Can Yoon-seo and Ju-won overcome obstacles and find their fairytale ending, or will reality tear them apart?

episodes.name: Goodbye, Seo Ju-won
episodes.overview: After dating Ju-won for a year and a half without knowing he was the youngest son of the AL Group family, Yoon-seo decides to break up with him at his mother's request while accepting her money. As promised, she attempts to break up with him by making him gradually resent her. However, she gets drunk and unknowingly calls him to break up.

episodes.name: A Declaration of War
episodes.overview: Now, as the AL CARD's director and Yoon-seo's superior, Ju-won declares war against Yoon-seo in an office he picked right next to hers. He vows he will never let her go and turns up his charms. He attacks her by flirting and clings to her in the most pitiful way. Meanwhile, Yoon-seo succumbs to his request to eat with him 27 times.

episodes.name: The Last Date
episodes.overview: Ju-won and Yoon-seo wake up both in despair after realising what they did and said to each other last night, intoxicated. They try to avoid one another at the company but end up face-to-face awkwardly. Meanwhile, Ju-won's mother reminds Yoon-seo of the promise she had made her, and Yoon-seo's brother gets into trouble at school for school bullying.

episodes.name: The Business Trip
episodes.overview: An unknown number keeps texting Yoon-seo's phone with messages only an ex-boyfriend would text, making her suspect Ju-won. When she confronts him about it, she makes a fool of herself. Meanwhile, the company's new venture in the vacation sector opens a hanok getaway where Yoon-seo's team and Ju-won go for a business trip.

episodes.name: The Anonymous Texter
episodes.overview: Ju-won leaves his family and shows up at Yoon-seo's door. His appearance exposes their relationship to the team, who even discover that their breakup was because of Ju-won's family's opposition, causing them to create an unbearable atmosphere for her in the office. Meanwhile, a crisis hits the Hanok Stay grand opening art exhibition, but Yoon-seo is away from her desk to handle it.

episodes.name: Can't Get Over Him
episodes.overview: Yoon-seo struggles to clarify her relationship with Ju Won, even though she knows it's over. Ju-won's lingering feelings make it even harder for her. On top of that, Seong-min unexpectedly enters her life, sparking Ju-won’s jealousy. Feeling overwhelmed, she lashes out at Seong-min’s frivolous words and actions.

episodes.name: Another Tactic
episodes.overview: While Yoon-seo and Seong-min seem to be getting closer, Ju-won becomes jealous and resorts to Si-won's advice of turning on his belligerent side. His sudden demeanor confuses Yoon-seo and frustrates her, angering her. But when she sees Ju-won with another woman, she is shocked by how flustered it made her.

episodes.name: The Marriage Proposal
episodes.overview: Ju-won shows up at Yoon-seo's mother's funeral. He's there for her once again, and she cries in his solace. Then, he surprises her with a marriage proposal, leaving her speechless. As he waits anxiously for her answer, circumstances force him to go to Spain, but Yoon-seo rushes to see him at the airport as if she will lose him forever.

episodes.name: Seeking Happiness
episodes.overview: Yoon-seo realises that before she can be honest about her relationship with Ju-won, there's something she needs to address first. Aware that the result might not be favourable, she decides to handle the situation on her own without involving Ju-won. Meanwhile, Si-won and Mi-jin are enjoying a wonderful night out together, but what starts as a moment of sincere honesty unexpectedly turns awkward.

episodes.name: A Cinderella Is Born
episodes.overview: While Ju-won and Yoon-seo enjoy the outdoors, the shocking news of Sun-joo's husband's affair in New York spreads. To remedy the shattered image of the company, Sun-joo allows Yoon-seo to marry Ju-won. However, she will expose Yoon-seo's impoverished background to show the humility of the conglomerate family. Ju-won learns about this and then charges to confront his mother angrily, but Yoon-seo stops him.
